Package modules

This package contains all of the Launch Pad application modules which is technologically powered by Swing and Core Java.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
GeneralDao An all purpose DAO Interface for serving all modules of the entire Launch Pad application.
 

Class Summary
GeneralDaoImpl The DAO implementation of the GeneralDao
GenericDateInputDialog Common modal dialog to capture the user's input regarding a date value.
GenericQtyInputDialog Common modal dialog to capture the user's input regarding a simple quantity value.
LaunchPad This is the main class and the main entry point of the Launch Pad application.
MainMenuCellRenderer Cell renderer for the Launch Pad main menu.
MainMenuItem A Value object managing the details of a menu item.
MainMenuListModelImpl Launch Pad's main menu implementation of ListModel which extends AbstarctLitModel.
SkuFinderDialog Modal dialog functioning to capturing the user's input of a SKU number.
StoreListDialog Dialog for displaying a list of stores and their servers for the purpose of allowing the user to select a server to establish a connection.
StoreListItem Value object for managing the details of a store list item.
StoreListItemComparator A Comparison implementation providing custom logic as to how two StoreListItem object values are compared to one another based on store number.
 

Exception Summary
LaunchPadException Exception class for general Launch Pad application errors.
 

Package modules Description

This package contains all of the Launch Pad application modules which is technologically powered by Swing and Core Java. Provides classes and interfaces that divides the Launch Pad application in to separate working modules. Launch Pad is comprised of the the following modules:

  • User Administration
  • Price Change Administration
  • Price Audit Administration
  • SI Transfers Administration
  • BI Tranfers Administration
  • SI RTV Administration
  • BI RTV Administration
  • Print Reprint Reports
  • Counts Administration
  • IDT Administration
  • Load Telnet Hex File
